Within this example, we display a Text component.<br><br>
var m = new <a href="<?php echo $documentation_path;?>/WIND.html" target="_blank">WIND</a>.<a href="<?php echo $documentation_path;?>/WIND.Text.html" target="_blank">Text</a>('<span id="param">Text</span>', <span id="param">{'<span id="options">top</span>':50,'<span id="options">left</span>':10,'<span id="options">height</span>':400,'<span id="options">width</span>':600,'<span id="options">color</span>':'#3366CC','<span id="options">border</span>':'#3366CC 2px solid','<span id="options">name</span>':'Text Displayer','<span id="options">icon</span>':'styles/images/tvizicon.png','<span id="options">draggable</span>':false,'<span id="options">resizable</span>':false,'<span id="options">header</span>':false,'<span id="options">removable</span>':false,'<span id="options">configurable</span>':false,'<span id="options">config</span>':true}</span>)<br><br>
All the given options have are the default values exept '<span id="options">top</span>':50 and '<span id="options">boxStyle</span>':true.<br>
The <span id="options">boxStyle</span> option means that we want to configure the text component from a menu.<br>
In the menu we can change the name and the color of the header and border.<br>
Although the <span id="options">header</span> option is set to false, the header will be displayed because <span id="options">boxStyle</span> is true.